9. GitLab tagging without manually commenting latest / test

Yes, stop manually commenting latest and test. Let the pipeline choose the tag.

Replace the hard-coded destination line:

--destination "$IMAGE_NAME:${TAG_VERSION}" \

with dynamic destinations.

A good first version:

variables:
  IMAGE_NAME: "registry.gitlab.us.lmco.com/lit/containers/pxe-content"
  DOCKER_FROM_IMAGE: "registry.gitlab.us.lmco.com/lit/containers/images/nginx-python-alpine:latest"
  DOCKER_AUTH_CONFIG: '{"auths":{"registry.gitlab.us.lmco.com":{"username":"RELEASE_TOKEN","password":"$RELEASE_TOKEN"}}}'
build_pxe_content:
  stage: build
  image:
    name: registry.gitlab.us.lmco.com/lit/containers/images/kaniko/kaniko:v1.23.0-debug
    entrypoint: [""]
  script:
    - |
      set -e
      DESTINATIONS="--destination ${IMAGE_NAME}:sha-${CI_COMMIT_SHORT_SHA}"
      if [ -n "${CI_COMMIT_TAG:-}" ]; then
        echo "Tag pipeline detected: ${CI_COMMIT_TAG}"
        DESTINATIONS="${DESTINATIONS} --destination ${IMAGE_NAME}:${CI_COMMIT_TAG} --destination ${IMAGE_NAME}:latest"
      elif [ "${CI_COMMIT_BRANCH:-}" = "${CI_DEFAULT_BRANCH:-main}" ]; then
        echo "Default branch pipeline detected"
        DESTINATIONS="${DESTINATIONS} --destination ${IMAGE_NAME}:latest --destination ${IMAGE_NAME}:main-${CI_COMMIT_SHORT_SHA}"
      elif [ "${CI_PIPELINE_SOURCE:-}" = "merge_request_event" ]; then
        echo "Merge request pipeline detected"
        DESTINATIONS="${DESTINATIONS} --destination ${IMAGE_NAME}:test --destination ${IMAGE_NAME}:mr-${CI_MERGE_REQUEST_IID} --destination ${IMAGE_NAME}:test-${CI_COMMIT_SHORT_SHA}"
      else
        echo "Branch pipeline detected"
        DESTINATIONS="${DESTINATIONS} --destination ${IMAGE_NAME}:test-${CI_COMMIT_REF_SLUG}"
      fi
      echo "Image destinations:"
      echo "${DESTINATIONS}" | tr ' ' '\n' | grep '^--destination' -A1 || true
      /kaniko/executor \
        --context "${CI_PROJECT_DIR}" \
        --dockerfile "${CI_PROJECT_DIR}/Dockerfile" \
        --build-arg DOCKER_FROM_IMAGE="${DOCKER_FROM_IMAGE}" \
        ${DESTINATIONS} \
        --cache=false

That gives you:

Pipeline type	Tags pushed
Merge request	test, mr-<iid>, test-<commit-sha>, sha-<commit-sha>
Default branch merge	latest, main-<commit-sha>, sha-<commit-sha>
Git tag pipeline	<git-tag>, latest, sha-<commit-sha>
Other branch	test-<branch-slug>, sha-<commit-sha>

For the “version tag when merged” part: I would not invent a fake semver in this pipeline yet. Use a real Git tag later from your existing release/versioning process. When the pipeline runs on CI_COMMIT_TAG, it will publish that version tag and latest.

So the flow becomes:

1. MR pipeline updates :test and :mr-58.
2. You test with:

podman run --rm --entrypoint /usr/local/bin/pxe-content-test registry.gitlab.us.lmco.com/lit/containers/pxe-content:test all

3. Merge to default branch updates :latest.
4. Release/tag pipeline updates :<version> and :latest.

That keeps testing, latest, and future versioned releases clean without manual edits.